.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A basic implementation of a shell in C.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIOPTION\fR]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsimple_shell\fR is a basic implementation of a shell that allows the user to execute commands in a command-line environment.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h, --help
Display help and information about available options.

.TP
.BR -v, --version
Display the current version of simple_shell.

.SH COMMANDS
.LP
\fBsimple_shell\fR supports the execution of system commands and provides some basic shell functionalities.

.LP
\fBexit\fR - Exit the shell.

.SH EXAMPLES
.LP
To execute a simple command:
.BR simple_shell " ls -l"

